==Parámetros de dificultad==
===Nº máximo de jugadores===
El número máximo de competidores de la IA ([[es/Manual/Configuración IA|Inteligencia artificial]]). Si está jugando una partida multijugador es posble que no quiera que sea demasiado alto para que otras personas no puedan unirse y tener su propia empresa. Su valor puede variar entre 0 y 14.

===Nº de pueblos===
How many towns there will be in the game. This is also affected by the map size. A very small map will never get lots of towns, while a large map will a lot more.
This can be set in two places (here in difficulty settings or in the new terragenesis panel) when set to high you will have lots of towns and more passengers.

===Nº de industrias===
How many towns there will be in the game. This is also affected by the map size. A very small map will never get lots of towns, while a large map will a lot more.
This is as the towns but this is for industries. This can be found on the ''generate map dialog'' too.

===Préstamo inicial máximo===
This is the maximum loan you can have at the start of the game. The amount slowly increases with game time.

===Tasa de interés inicial===
This is the % of the loan you will be paying each game year. This doesn't pay off the loan itself.

===Costes de operación de vehículo===
This is the cost per game year that all your vehicles have to pay. 

===Velocidad de construcción de la competencia===
This is how fast the AI competitors build. If this is set too high they will have a giant network running in no time.

===Averías de vehículos===
This is how often your vehicles breakdown.

===Multiplicador de subvenciones===
How much the income is multiplied on a subsidy service.

===Coste de la construcción===
This is how expensive it is for you to build anything and terraform the land.

===Tipo de terreno===
How the land is formed from flat to mountainous. This can be found on the ''generate map dialog'' too.

===Cantidad de mar/lagos===
This is how much of the map is taken up by the water. This can be found on the ''generate map dialog'' too.

===Economía===
If the economy isn't set to steady, it may go into a recession, which causes the industries to produce only half as much then usual. 

===Marcha atrás trenes===
This specifies trains can reverse, either at station, or only at the end of a line. Even with this set to "Only at end of line" a player can hit the "turnaround" button on the train interface to turn the train around.

===Desastres===
This specifies if [[en/Manual/Disasters]] are on or off.

===Actitud de las autoridades ante cambios en el terreno===
This is how willing a local authority is to let you build near and in their town.

